During first field practice student gets overview about the organisation, its main regulations, rules, norms, clients, problems. Students meets clients or explores process of social policy. During four weeks student observes the client s, their main problems and solutions for the target groups. `To observe`doesnt mean that student cant participate but the participation is based on the trust between practice supervisor and student and also depends on the place where observational practice is going to happen. Student is obliged to to reflect upon the process during the field practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to give basic knowledge about social work practice in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Is able to set the goals for field practice; Is able to describe main social problems in Estonia; Is able to name main client groups and services, benefits to help them; Is able to analyse his(her) own activities in organisation; Is able to reflect on self development during the practice; Is able to find relevant laws, plans and other documents; Is able to describe to functions of the organisation; Gets first experience in getting contact with welfare organisations.
